Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.35,0:00:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello everyone, and welcome
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.13,0:00:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to Building Apps with Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.57,0:00:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.43,0:00:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Clare, and together
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with my colleague Nandini, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.44,0:00:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,excited to share with you how
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.58,0:00:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make your apps work
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.03,0:00:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,great at any text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.18,0:00:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we'll first cover what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.88,0:00:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type is and why the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,feature exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.45,0:00:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Next we'll look at what's new in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.65,0:00:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.10,0:00:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll follow that with some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.14,0:00:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines and API you can apply
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.87,0:00:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to your own apps, and finally
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.86,0:00:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll show all of that hands-on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.39,0:00:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in a sample app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.42,0:01:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So first what is Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.68,0:01:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type is a feature that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.61,0:01:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,allows users to customize the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.69,0:01:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,size of text on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.94,0:01:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, some users may
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.29,0:01:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,prefer a smaller text size so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.63,0:01:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they can fit more content on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.17,0:01:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Others may prefer a larger text
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.67,0:01:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,size because it's more
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.60,0:01:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But Dynamic Type goes beyond a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,user's preferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.24,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Some users may experience eye
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.95,0:01:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,strain when viewing text at the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.85,0:01:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,default size for long periods of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.88,0:01:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Others may simply have less
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,acute vision due to aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet others may have a low
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.03,0:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,vision condition which makes it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible for them to read text
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.28,0:01:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,at the default size.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.46,0:01:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So for these users Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:01:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't just a preference, it's an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.86,0:02:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,actual need and by supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.26,0:02:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type in your apps, you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.94,0:02:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,can allow these users to use
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.65,0:02:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your app and have a great
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.44,0:02:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,experience with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.05,0:02:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dynamic Type settings can be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.47,0:02:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,found in the Settings app under
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Display and Brightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.74,0:02:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts out with seven
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,different text sizes you can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.98,0:02:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,choose from, and the default one
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also go into your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.31,0:02:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility settings and there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.99,0:02:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you can enable five even larger
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.82,0:02:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.07,0:02:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Those sizes are geared towards
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.76,0:02:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,users with low vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They range from somewhat larger
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.31,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than default size to much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, looking at this you might
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.75,0:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,be wondering whether you really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,need text to get that big.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.24,0:02:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look in the example of why
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.91,0:02:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,this is useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the phone app and on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.38,0:02:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the left we've got it at the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,largest size, not including the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right we have it at the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,larger size overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.19,0:03:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at this through
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the lens of a user with low
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.81,0:03:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.05,0:03:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone with low vision might
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.22,0:03:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,see something closer to what we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.47,0:03:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how the version on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.43,0:03:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,left is completely unreadable,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but the version on the right is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.79,0:03:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,still fairly readable, even
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,though its blurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.07,0:03:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So text size makes a huge
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.71,0:03:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,difference for the legibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.43,0:03:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps and that's why it's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.73,0:03:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really important that you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.63,0:03:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,support the full range of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.09,0:03:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.22,0:03:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what Dynamic Type is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and now let's look at what's new
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.77,0:03:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 11 for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.29,0:03:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest thing that's changed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.60,0:03:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is that Dynamic Type support is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.34,0:03:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,vastly improved and expanded
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.27,0:03:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,across all of iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When we started working on iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,11, we had three goals in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,First, text should be large
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.72,0:04:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,enough for the user to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.85,0:04:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, text should
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.10,0:04:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,scale with Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.95,0:04:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, the text should be fully
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.93,0:04:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,readable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be truncated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.98,0:04:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,unnecessarily and it shouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.71,0:04:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,be overlapped or clipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.28,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, we want an app UI to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,look beautiful at all text
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.49,0:04:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.71,0:04:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for more information on the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.42,0:04:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,design thinking behind the iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,11 Dynamic Type improvements,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.05,0:04:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,please check out the Design for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.17,0:04:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone talk from yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's look at some
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,examples of what's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the Settings app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how it now adapts
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,beautifully for all the text
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.57,0:04:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's another example from
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.15,0:04:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how text everywhere is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.55,0:04:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,scaling with Dynamic Type, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.58,0:04:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,some texts, like the event time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.41,0:04:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is laid out differently to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate larger text.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.05,0:05:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are some cases where
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't scale for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in tab bars, if we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.35,0:05:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,were to scale a text here, the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,tab bar would take away too much
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.39,0:05:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,room from the main content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.35,0:05:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,However, now, in iOS 11, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.23,0:05:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have one of the five largest
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type settings chosen,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can long press on one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,items in the tab bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the Voicemail tab,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and that will show a larger
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.15,0:05:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,version in the middle of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.83,0:05:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a sampling of what's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.28,0:05:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,changed in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.87,0:05:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at some
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.87,0:05:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines in API that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,apply to your own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be covering this in four
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.59,0:05:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.87,0:05:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we'll look at how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.34,0:05:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,scale your font sizes for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.66,0:05:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.60,0:05:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we'll see how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate larger text in your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,app's layouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.44,0:05:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, we'll look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.75,0:05:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,specific, very common case of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.46,0:05:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,table views.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.30,0:05:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, we'll even see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.73,0:06:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how images can work well with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.68,0:06:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, let's scale font sizes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.62,0:06:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.92,0:06:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The easiest way to do this is to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.67,0:06:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,use the built-in text styles
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.53,0:06:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that come with iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.32,0:06:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a list of all of our text
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.65,0:06:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,styles, along with their font
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes at the default text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.75,0:06:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If your user has a different
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,text size selected, these font
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes will also change.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for those of you who have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.46,0:06:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,already be using text styles in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.80,0:06:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your app, first, thank you; and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,second, there's one important
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.13,0:06:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,change in iOS 11 that you should
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.46,0:06:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,be aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.03,0:06:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to iOS 11 all the text
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.48,0:06:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,style adapted for the seven
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.17,0:06:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,standard sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, only the body style
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,adapted for the five
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.84,0:06:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 all of the text style
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:06:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,adapt for all 12 text sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if you're using text
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,styles, you'll get support for
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.25,0:07:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all 12 sizes for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.05,0:07:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To use text styles in Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.12,0:07:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Builder, go to the Attribute
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.76,0:07:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector and change the font on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.76,0:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,your view.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.26,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By default this will be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,something like System 17 point,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.67,0:07:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which means it's not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.71,0:07:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,scale with Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.47,0:07:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you click on that T icon,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.19,0:07:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you can choose one of the text
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,style fonts instead and those
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.06,0:07:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, new in iOS 11 you can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.99,0:07:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,check the Automatically Adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Font checkbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.19,0:07:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that if the user
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.40,0:07:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,changes their text size while
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is running, your view
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,will automatically update its
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.15,0:07:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,font for the new text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we highly recommend you check
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this on all of your views.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.38,0:07:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In code it's just as easy to use
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.30,0:07:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,text styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.76,0:07:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredFont(forTextStyle) API
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:07:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a font for the text
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,style, and then you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.30,0:08:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,adjustsFontForContentSize
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.93,0:08:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Category property to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.99,0:08:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that your views update their
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts if the text size changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.13,0:08:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if you can't use text
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,styles?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you have a design that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.48,0:08:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,requires custom fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.77,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The great news is that in iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.03,0:08:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really easy to get those
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.80,0:08:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts to work well with Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.87,0:08:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.24,0:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say you have some code
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.79,0:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that assigns the font property
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.03,0:08:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of a label to a custom font of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.43,0:08:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 you can now use the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.17,0:08:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,new UIFontMetrics class to scale
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.11,0:08:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that font so that it will get
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.47,0:08:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller or bigger, depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the user's text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.23,0:08:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.52,0:08:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.55,0:08:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example we're using the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.77,0:08:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,default font metrics, which
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.35,0:08:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,means we're using the font
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.83,0:08:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,metrics of the body text style.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.78,0:08:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that if body text
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.84,0:09:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,would be 50 percent larger for a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,particular user, your font will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,also get 50 percent larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.51,0:09:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For better results, you can pick
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.26,0:09:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a particular text style that you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,want to scale your font with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.62,0:09:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.77,0:09:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,font that you're using for title
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.34,0:09:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,text in your app, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.91,0:09:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,choose to scale it in the same
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.47,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,way that we've scaled title1
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.20,0:09:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a final word on web views.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.39,0:09:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you may have web views
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.91,0:09:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're displaying in your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.05,0:09:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.10,0:09:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You should make those adapt for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.59,0:09:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.16,0:09:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so, you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.78,0:09:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-apple-system-body font and that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,will get you the body text style
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.87,0:09:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,font and it will adapt for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,user's dynamic typesetting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.16,0:09:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, note that this is only
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.19,0:09:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,available on Apple devices, so
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.90,0:09:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're planning to use the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.86,0:09:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,same web page for other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.87,0:09:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,platforms, make sure you set an
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.75,0:09:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate fallback font.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then for your other styles you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.08,0:09:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,can define their font sizes in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.63,0:09:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,terms of relative units, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:09:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that way they'll scale
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.54,0:09:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,proportionately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how you can scale your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,font sizes for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.25,0:10:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodate larger text in your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.48,0:10:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,app layouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.22,0:10:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say we've got some text
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at the default text size, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you can imagine that the white
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.74,0:10:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,border is the available area on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.36,0:10:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So first step, let's scale the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.09,0:10:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,font size.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.17,0:10:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.26,0:10:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The text is now running off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,screen and so your users are not
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.41,0:10:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,going to see anything outside of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.35,0:10:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the white box.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.64,0:10:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To prevent the label from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.56,0:10:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,running off screen, we can add a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.40,0:10:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.24,0:10:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we still have a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because the text is getting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.89,0:10:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,truncated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.68,0:10:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The end result is that your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.97,0:10:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,users aren't going to see all
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.30,0:10:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To really fix this let's wrap
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the text and that will allow the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.31,0:10:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,text to grow as much as it needs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.70,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,while still displaying all of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.51,0:10:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.13,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To wrap text in Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Builder you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Attribute Inspector and adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.51,0:11:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lines property on your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,label.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.08,0:11:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,By default this is set to one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.31,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,line, but if you change it to 0,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that will allow your label to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,wrap to as many lines as it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,needs for its content.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.12,0:11:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do the same thing in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.35,0:11:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,code by setting the number of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,lines property to 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.27,0:11:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Let's look at another
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.59,0:11:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,common scenario that can occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you're writing your app
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're thinking about the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.89,0:11:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,default text size, it's tempting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.50,0:11:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to use constant values for your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,spacings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.33,0:11:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So you might have something like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.42,0:11:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,two labels here whose baselines
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.61,0:11:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,are separated by a constant 40
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.81,0:11:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks great at the default text
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.41,0:11:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,size, but once you start
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,adapting for Dynamic Type, you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,can run into problems like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.12,0:11:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where the labels overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What we really want here is a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,spacing that's dynamic and that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.74,0:12:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,accounts for the fonts involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.09,0:12:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 you can now do this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with new Auto Layout System
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Spacing Constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can define the spacing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,between two baselines and Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.57,0:12:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout will automatically figure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.88,0:12:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,out the best spacing to use
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.03,0:12:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the fonts of your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.04,0:12:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,viewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.98,0:12:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you try this and you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.82,0:12:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,decide that you want a slightly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.49,0:12:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,larger or smaller spacing, you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can do that, too, by adjusting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.15,0:12:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the Multiplier property and that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.71,0:12:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,will let you get the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.77,0:12:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,results you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also possible to use these
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.55,0:12:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,new Auto Layout Constraints in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder, and for more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.63,0:12:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,information on that, please
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the Auto Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.23,0:12:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Techniques and Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,talk that happened this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.16,0:12:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I know there are probably
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.32,0:12:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,some of you out there who have a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,view in your app that was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.89,0:13:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,written eight or nine years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's just not using Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.76,0:13:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.54,0:13:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, we have you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.69,0:13:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.85,0:13:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say you have some
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,layout code that sets a constant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,value and ads that to a y
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.78,0:13:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.35,0:13:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the same UIFontMetrics
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.48,0:13:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,class we saw earlier we can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.56,0:13:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,scale that 40 point value, or
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.56,0:13:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,any CGFloat value, and that way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it will get smaller or larger,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the user's text
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.85,0:13:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,size.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at one final
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.67,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,common scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we've got two labels that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.36,0:13:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are side-by-side at the default
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.20,0:13:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.48,0:13:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you can imagine that the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,yellow border is the area
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.41,0:13:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,available on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.62,0:13:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's scale our font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.53,0:13:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, there's not
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.75,0:13:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,enough room for the text
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.76,0:13:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore, so going back to what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.91,0:13:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw earlier, we could try to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.08,0:13:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wrap the text --
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.05,0:14:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll get something like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.79,0:14:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.33,0:14:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd like to step back for a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,second and revisit those three
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,goals we mentioned at the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.49,0:14:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning of the talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.35,0:14:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,First, all text should be large
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.85,0:14:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.55,0:14:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got that covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, all text should be fully
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.85,0:14:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,readable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.93,0:14:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,None of the text is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, app UI should look
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.34,0:14:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful at all text sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.46,0:14:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where we haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.56,0:14:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,quite met our goals yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, on the righthand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.40,0:14:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,side the d is being orphaned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from the rest of the word and it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just doesn't look right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.79,0:14:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So for this scenario we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.48,0:14:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,recommend that for larger font
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes you change your layout to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.02,0:14:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,use vertical stacking and that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.06,0:14:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,way each label can grow to the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.40,0:14:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,full width of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this technique works not
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.31,0:14:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just for text, but for anything
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.94,0:14:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that might take room away from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.35,0:14:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.66,0:15:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, here's the Siri
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.11,0:15:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Help screen and notice how on
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the left, at the default text
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,size, there's an icon that takes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.33,0:15:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,up a horizontal column away from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.35,0:15:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why for larger font
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes we actually move that icon
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,above the text and allow the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.61,0:15:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,text to grow to the full width
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to do an alternate layout
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.79,0:15:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the user's text size
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.31,0:15:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll need to know how to get
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.32,0:15:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.51,0:15:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that by accessing the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.23,0:15:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredConstantSizeCategory
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.05,0:15:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,property on either your view's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.17,0:15:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,traitCollection or on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,UIApplication object.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The default text size will
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,return large and the standard
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes run from extra small to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.92,0:15:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,extra, extra, extra large.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Accessibility sizes are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:15:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,prefixed with Accessibility to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:15:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid adding more extras.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in iOS 11 we've added new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.13,0:16:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,functions that you can use to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.38,0:16:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ask questions about the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.79,0:16:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, you can check
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.98,0:16:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the user is using one of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.14,0:16:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the Accessibility text sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and if so, you can do an
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate layout like vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,stacking,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can use any threshold you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.51,0:16:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,want.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.53,0:16:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We now support compares in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.75,0:16:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,operators so you can check
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.20,0:16:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the user's text size is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.64,0:16:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,larger than a particular
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,threshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.28,0:16:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So that covers some general
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.44,0:16:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines for adapting your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.62,0:16:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,layouts for Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.97,0:16:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at the specific
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.82,0:16:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,case of table views.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.62,0:16:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier we saw how the Settings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.95,0:16:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,app adapts beautifully for all
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.10,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news is that if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,using a standard table view
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.46,0:16:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,styles, you will get this kind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.02,0:16:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of layout for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So your fonts will grow or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.17,0:16:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,shrink, depending on the Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:16:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Type setting, and for larger
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.32,0:17:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts the text will wrap so that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.44,0:17:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it is visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.71,0:17:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, for standard table views
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that have a detail text label,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,those will automatically lay out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.66,0:17:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with vertical stacking for
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.31,0:17:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,larger fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.27,0:17:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So standard table views will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.42,0:17:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,adapt their layout for Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Type, and cell heights are based
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.18,0:17:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,on their content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.70,0:17:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is particularly important
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.01,0:17:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at larger font sizes where the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.56,0:17:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,text wraps because a cell that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has more text may need to be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.17,0:17:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,taller than a cell that has
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.22,0:17:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,less.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do we accomplish variable
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,cell heights in a table view?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.10,0:17:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this through a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.06,0:17:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,technique called self-sizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When self-sizing is enabled, the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.35,0:17:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,table view will ask each cell to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,provide its own size and the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,cell can calculate that based on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.81,0:17:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,its own content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.24,0:17:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the table view client
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,simply needs to give the table
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.43,0:17:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,view an estimate for any cells
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.74,0:17:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that are off screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 self-sizing is enabled
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.24,0:18:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you're using fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,row heights or if you are using
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Builder, you may need
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.94,0:18:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to enable self-sizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.80,0:18:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so set your row height of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.85,0:18:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a table view to be Automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.52,0:18:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dimension and then set the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.52,0:18:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Estimated Row Height to a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.17,0:18:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable estimate given your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.63,0:18:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,table view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have section headers and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.52,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,footers, you can do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thing for those using very
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.56,0:18:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,similarly named properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.35,0:18:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the story for standard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.83,0:18:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,table view cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.14,0:18:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're using custom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.62,0:18:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cells with Auto Layout, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.53,0:18:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,really easy to get these to work
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with self-sizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need to do is set up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,your constraints so that they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.78,0:18:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,define the size of the cell and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,then Auto Layout will figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the size for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.07,0:18:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's look at how we could
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.03,0:18:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,set up the constraints for this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.37,0:19:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,custom cell shown here, where we
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.13,0:19:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,have two labels, one on top of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.77,0:19:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.36,0:19:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely want leading
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and trailing constraints for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.05,0:19:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,those labels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.42,0:19:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.03,0:19:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the labels are separated
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.12,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,vertically by an appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.79,0:19:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you can use the new
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.19,0:19:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,System Spacing Constraints to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.31,0:19:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,get a value that will work well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.84,0:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at all text sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.96,0:19:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So are we done?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.19,0:19:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.70,0:19:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We still need to add constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.30,0:19:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,relative to the top and bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.01,0:19:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the cell and that will
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.93,0:19:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,complete the set of constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to define the size of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.44,0:19:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you can use the System
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.80,0:19:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Spacing Constraints here to get
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,values that will look good
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.04,0:19:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,across all text sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:19:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're using Manual
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.24,0:19:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout with your cells, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.61,0:19:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,also use self-sizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.63,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so you'll want to override
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:19:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the sizeThatFits method on your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.39,0:20:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,cell, and then you can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.56,0:20:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,contentView's width to figure
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.87,0:20:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,out the width available for your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.73,0:20:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,subviews.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.18,0:20:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's move on to our last
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.68,0:20:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,topic, images.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.36,0:20:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are images showing up in a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about Dynamic Type?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they're not text.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.87,0:20:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But images are an integral part
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.46,0:20:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of your app's UI and in some
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,cases they carry meaning that's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,not communicated elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.11,0:20:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the same reason it's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,important for your text to be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.04,0:20:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,readable by your users, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,also important that your images
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.44,0:20:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are distinguishable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.14,0:20:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the Recents view in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the phone app.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.58,0:20:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how in front of some of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.90,0:20:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the calls there's an image of a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,phone with an arrow pointing out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.85,0:20:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This image means that this call
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.36,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was made by you versus a call
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.95,0:21:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.13,0:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's turn up the text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.49,0:21:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you who are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.39,0:21:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,wondering, the image has moved
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.14,0:21:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,over here and notice how it is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.53,0:21:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,tiny compared to the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need your text to be this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.81,0:21:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,big so you can read it, you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.83,0:21:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,probably can't see that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.40,0:21:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we really want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.62,0:21:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,here is scale the image the same
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.32,0:21:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,way that we scale a text, and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.38,0:21:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that's exactly what we've done
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 11, and better yet, we
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.70,0:21:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,made it easy for you to do so in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.28,0:21:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So to just allow your images to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,scale for Dynamic Type you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.99,0:21:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,first want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,your images are provided as
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,PDF's at 1x scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.42,0:21:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a good idea anyways
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because it allows you to use the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.15,0:21:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,same image for both 2x and 3x
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.83,0:21:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,resolution devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, your app might already
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.22,0:21:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,be doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.76,0:21:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So just make sure you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.03,0:21:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,PDF.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.94,0:21:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, go to the Asset Catalog
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.67,0:22:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and check this new checkbox for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.53,0:22:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Preserving Vector Data.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't check the checkbox,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.09,0:22:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Asset Catalog is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.13,0:22:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,compiled, it's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.52,0:22:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,rasterize all the PDF's.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.66,0:22:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you check the checkbox,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.86,0:22:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the original PDF gets preserved,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.68,0:22:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cool thing about that is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that now if you use this image
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.90,0:22:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it into an image view of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.46,0:22:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,any size, the image will get
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.58,0:22:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,drawn smoothly using PDF
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.83,0:22:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.52,0:22:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.08,0:22:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the final step is to make
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.44,0:22:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that your view resizes for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.00,0:22:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.17,0:22:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this in Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.43,0:22:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you can select any image view or
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.85,0:22:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,button and you can check the new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.23,0:22:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Adjusts Image Size property.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.76,0:22:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that your image
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.08,0:22:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,viewer button will scale up for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.36,0:22:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the five largest Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.81,0:22:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.12,0:22:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do the same thing in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.28,0:22:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,code with the Adjusts Image Size
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.87,0:22:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.99,0:23:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,AccessibilityContentSizeCategory
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.24,0:23:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one more place where
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.79,0:23:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,image scaling comes in handy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.05,0:23:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's when the user long
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.25,0:23:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,presses on a bar item.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.61,0:23:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So earlier we saw how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.37,0:23:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,long press on the Voicemail tab
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.90,0:23:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to show a larger version in the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.14,0:23:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.43,0:23:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that both the text is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.94,0:23:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,scaling and also the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.15,0:23:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.41,0:23:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that image looks as good as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.53,0:23:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.54,0:23:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If your bar item is using a PDF
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.80,0:23:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,image, all you need to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.67,0:23:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,check the Preserve Vector Data
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.95,0:23:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,checkbox that we saw earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.16,0:23:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That will allow UIKit to scale
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.22,0:23:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it up smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.28,0:23:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not using a PDF,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.07,0:23:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll want to provide a larger
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,version that we can show when
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.23,0:23:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the user long presses on that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.86,0:23:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,image.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To do that in Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.83,0:23:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you can go to the Attributes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.90,0:23:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector and set the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.73,0:24:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility property of your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.21,0:24:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,bar item to be the larger
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.73,0:24:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,version.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.05,0:24:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Or in code you can simply set
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.47,0:24:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the largeContentSizeImage
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.01,0:24:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,property to that larger version.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.54,0:24:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've just covered a variety
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.25,0:24:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of tips and tricks you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.94,0:24:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to adapt your apps for Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.17,0:24:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.92,0:24:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I'd like to invite
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nandini to the stage to show all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.47,0:24:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of that in a sample app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.09,0:24:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.46,0:24:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Nandini.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.35,0:24:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a software engineer in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.70,0:24:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Team at Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.38,0:24:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, using a sample app, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.47,0:24:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,show you how you can fix your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.45,0:24:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,app in very little time with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.07,0:24:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.39,0:24:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I will open the app in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.37,0:24:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the default text size, and later
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.10,0:24:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll open the app in the largest
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.06,0:24:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Dynamic Type font size
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.29,0:24:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and fix issues along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.23,0:24:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.21,0:24:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We cleared it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.63,0:24:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Cute Battle Pets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.68,0:25:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In this app you can choose among
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.26,0:25:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,two pets to battle with each
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.55,0:25:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.40,0:25:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me open the app now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.12,0:25:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In this tab, Opponents, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.35,0:25:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a list of pets you can choose to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.10,0:25:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,battle among each other, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.40,0:25:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,next tab, Achievements, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.72,0:25:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a list of badges of honors these
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.67,0:25:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,pets can earn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.99,0:25:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Before auditing our app for the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.48,0:25:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,largest of the Dynamic Type font
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.53,0:25:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,size, if we switch back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.87,0:25:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Opponents tab, you can audit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.73,0:25:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your app for the largest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.39,0:25:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Font size using a very
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.20,0:25:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,handy tool in Xcode called
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.10,0:25:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.96,0:25:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This tool is very handy because
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.02,0:25:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can audit your app before
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.56,0:25:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,going to the Settings app on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.46,0:25:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your device.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.36,0:25:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can open this tool by going
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.64,0:25:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to Xcode in the menu bar, choose
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.98,0:25:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Open Developer Tool and then
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.45,0:25:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,click on Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.58,0:25:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.21,0:25:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This tool can be used to audit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.01,0:25:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,apps in all macOS and iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.56,0:26:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhones, including the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.01,0:26:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Simulators.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.52,0:26:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As our app is running on the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.84,0:26:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone Simulator, I'll choose
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.23,0:26:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Start from the dropdown menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.89,0:26:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go to the Settings tab in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.25,0:26:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the Accessibility Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.68,0:26:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see a font size slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.58,0:26:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The font size is currently the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.86,0:26:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,default text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.46,0:26:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to move the slider's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.83,0:26:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,knob to the last notch on the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.33,0:26:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,slider.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.01,0:26:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the largest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.11,0:26:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type font size.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.01,0:26:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to our app now to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.37,0:26:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see the effect of this change.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.96,0:26:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The font size of these labels
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.52,0:26:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has not changed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.40,0:26:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Any idea why this is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.08,0:26:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is happening because of two
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.35,0:26:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The labels here are not yet set
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.42,0:26:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to automatically adjust to the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.96,0:26:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,user's ContentSizeCategory, and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.05,0:26:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the petName and petDescription
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.46,0:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,labels here are using custom
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.88,0:26:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.46,0:26:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to a project now to fix
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.99,0:26:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,these issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.26,0:26:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll minimize Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.29,0:26:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.20,0:27:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go to BattleCell zip file.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.43,0:27:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, using the jump bar, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.37,0:27:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,move to Set Up Labels and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.35,0:27:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Buttons Method.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.69,0:27:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here for petName, petDescription
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.98,0:27:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and battleButton's titleLabel,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.88,0:27:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll set the property at this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.73,0:27:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,font for ContentSizeCategory and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.45,0:27:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll set it to True.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.25,0:27:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As petName and petDescription
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.62,0:27:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are using custom fonts, we can
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.77,0:27:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,use UIFont, make it API, scan
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.15,0:27:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,font for font metric.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.04,0:27:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,For petName I'll be using the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.13,0:27:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,headline TextStyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.28,0:27:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For petDescription I'll be using
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.32,0:27:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the sub headline TextStyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.38,0:27:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run the app again and see
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.25,0:27:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.52,0:28:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after these labels are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.64,0:28:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusted to the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.89,0:28:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ContentSizeCategory, we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.28,0:28:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,these labels have really less
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.74,0:28:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal room to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.85,0:28:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,With the menu on the left and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.32,0:28:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the button on the right, these
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.40,0:28:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,labels have really less
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.69,0:28:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal room to grow and the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.58,0:28:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,labels either truncate or wrap
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.52,0:28:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in multiple lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.08,0:28:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can fix this by having an
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.83,0:28:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate adopt layout for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.80,0:28:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,larger text constraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.21,0:28:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We can achieve this by moving
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.14,0:28:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the image above the text and the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.04,0:28:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,button below the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.56,0:28:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This will ensure that the labels
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.38,0:28:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are less of wrap and truncated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.14,0:28:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go fix this in our project
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.77,0:28:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.08,0:28:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,First, before adding this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.97,0:28:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,adoptLayoutConstraints for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.25,0:28:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,larger text constraints, let me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.36,0:28:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,add a private variable for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.12,0:28:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Next let me go to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.76,0:29:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,setupLayoutConstraints method.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.58,0:29:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see that you already
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.92,0:29:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have a set of layout constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.43,0:29:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for default text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.63,0:29:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'll be placing a set of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.15,0:29:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints for larger Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.45,0:29:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Type font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.05,0:29:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These set of constraints pasted
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.74,0:29:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,here will be available in the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.90,0:29:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,sample app code attached along
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.39,0:29:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the session website.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.67,0:29:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go and review this after
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.37,0:29:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the session, but I give a short
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,overview of what this actually
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.73,0:29:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.41,0:29:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,These constraints ensure that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.64,0:29:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the image labels and the button
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.44,0:29:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are vertically stacked, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.95,0:29:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,these constraints also get them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.82,0:29:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the height of the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.59,0:29:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Let's go to our
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.11,0:29:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,developerLayoutConstraints
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.62,0:29:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,method.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.03,0:29:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we see that one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.36,0:29:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,developer constraints aren't
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.35,0:29:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.39,0:29:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We need the larger [inaudible],
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.11,0:29:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.25,0:29:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's fix that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.05,0:29:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, based on user's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.22,0:30:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredContentSizeCategory,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.92,0:30:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they put in the five largest
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.98,0:30:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.78,0:30:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,With the app you will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.75,0:30:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,look at its constraints and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.88,0:30:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,activateLargeTextConstraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.25,0:30:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, do the reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.50,0:30:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.29,0:30:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To ensure that these layout
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.96,0:30:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints are up-to-date based
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.07,0:30:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on the change in trait
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.06,0:30:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,collection, we call this method
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.91,0:30:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if trait collection did change.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.08,0:30:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.75,0:30:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredContentSizeCategory
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.97,0:30:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,shifts from the five largest
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type font sizes to the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.16,0:30:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller Dynamic Type font sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.80,0:30:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or visa-versa, these layout
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.02,0:30:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints will be updated.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.54,0:30:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run the app again to see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.23,0:30:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.27,0:30:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. After vertically stacking
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.35,0:30:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the content the labels are less
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.40,0:30:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of wrapped and there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.26,0:30:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,truncation at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.57,0:31:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go the next step,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.06,0:31:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.36,0:31:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When we run the app in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.81,0:31:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,default text size, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.53,0:31:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,notice that these cells here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.09,0:31:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,have multiple lines of text, but
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,currently only one line of text
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.17,0:31:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is visible on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.37,0:31:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to Achievements View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.65,0:31:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller in Swift check on why
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.34,0:31:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.18,0:31:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is happening because the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.27,0:31:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,table view's row height is set
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.83,0:31:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to a constant value, hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.04,0:31:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes that these cells do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.52,0:31:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,not have cell size at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.10,0:31:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To fix this and make this cells
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.77,0:31:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,have size we have to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.16,0:31:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,table view's row height to use
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.98,0:31:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,UITableViewAutomaticDimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.76,0:31:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and TableView's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.69,0:31:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,estimatedRowHeight to a constant
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.21,0:31:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,value, and I'll choose hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.12,0:31:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run the app again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.14,0:31:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go to Achievements tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.85,0:32:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we see that we have more
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.94,0:32:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,lines of text in each of these
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.48,0:32:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,cells, and the cells, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.83,0:32:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,sized to fit content, but let's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.99,0:32:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look at the [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.04,0:32:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike the labels the images do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not grow, according to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.11,0:32:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,user's ContentSizeCategory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.93,0:32:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To fix this let's go to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.13,0:32:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Achievements [inaudible] file.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.26,0:32:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And set the label and image view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.43,0:32:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,method.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.75,0:32:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For the badgeImageView I set the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.87,0:32:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,property adjustsImageSize for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.97,0:32:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityContentSize
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.15,0:32:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Category, and I set it to two.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.83,0:32:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This will ensure that the image
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.64,0:32:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is scaled for the five largest
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.10,0:32:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.06,0:32:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run the app again to see
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.02,0:32:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of this change.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.52,0:33:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me move to Achievements tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.22,0:33:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. Both the labels and the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.90,0:33:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,image have sizes largest Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.81,0:33:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Type font size, but let's take a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.16,0:33:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,closer look at the image in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.41,0:33:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,these cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.24,0:33:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's also take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.16,0:33:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,large text only that comes up in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.24,0:33:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a long press on the tab bar
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.43,0:33:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.38,0:33:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on that, the images in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.26,0:33:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,these cells and also in the tab
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.31,0:33:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,bar icons were not smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.86,0:33:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To fix that we have to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.56,0:33:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Assets Catalog, choose our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.60,0:33:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,images, those are PDF images, go
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.55,0:33:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Attributes Inspector and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.64,0:33:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,click on the Preserve Vector
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.60,0:33:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Data checkbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.36,0:34:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do this, what happens is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.26,0:34:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the PDF vector data is preserved
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.93,0:34:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the images are rendered
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.85,0:34:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,smooth in different Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.38,0:34:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.45,0:34:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run the app again to see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.40,0:34:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of this change.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.13,0:34:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go to Achievements tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.34,0:34:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For confirmation, let me zoom in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.80,0:34:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.17,0:34:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we see that the images here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.00,0:34:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,are rendered smooth, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.39,0:34:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, using the Accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.77,0:34:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, I'm going to run
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.29,0:34:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,through a quick audit of this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.25,0:34:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,app and different Dynamic Type
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.93,0:34:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.90,0:34:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For that let me minimize Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.36,0:34:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me bring up the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.76,0:34:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.17,0:34:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me move the first tab,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.67,0:34:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.01,0:35:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me switch the font size
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.84,0:35:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,slider to default text size.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.19,0:35:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to increase the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.54,0:35:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,font size one-by-one and you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.39,0:35:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,notice that the labels in these
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.97,0:35:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,cells increase according to the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.44,0:35:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,user's ContentSizeCategory.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.70,0:35:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When I move to the five larger
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.06,0:35:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type font sizes, the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.05,0:35:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,layout of these cells change.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.73,0:35:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The labels have more horizontal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.31,0:35:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,room to grow and the cell says
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.50,0:35:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sizeToFitContent.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.20,0:35:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Next move on to Achievements to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.44,0:35:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,do the same audit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.44,0:35:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll switch back to default text
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.88,0:35:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,size.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll increase the font size
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.65,0:35:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,one-by-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.74,0:35:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you see that the labels
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.67,0:35:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,wrap in multiple lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.35,0:35:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The cell says sizeToFitContent,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.76,0:35:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and also the image scales in the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.26,0:35:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,five larger Dynamic Type font
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.62,0:35:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.26,0:35:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.23,0:35:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our app looks pretty great in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.38,0:36:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all the Dynamic Type font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.68,0:36:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So using the new API's available
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.61,0:36:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 11, you can make your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.14,0:36:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,apps, too, work for all Dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.37,0:36:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Type font sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.95,0:36:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I welcome Clare back on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.55,0:36:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,stage to conclude the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.31,0:36:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.76,0:36:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.52,0:36:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.11,0:36:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Nandini.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.92,0:36:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of that sample code is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.67,0:36:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,available on our session
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.19,0:36:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,website, but the version we have
